  "description": "Evaluating AI used to mean just checking if the model gave the correct answer—but once AI becomes agentic, that mental model completely breaks down.                                  \n                                                                                                                                                      \n  In this video, I break down:                                                                                                                                                          \n  • Why autonomous agents break traditional NLP benchmarks        \n  • The critical shift from evaluating \"Outputs\" to evaluating \"Trajectories\"                                                                                                           \n  • How trace grading and LLM-as-a-Judge actually work                                                                                                                                  \n  • The architecture of a modern Eval-Driven Development stack\n  • Why evals are becoming the operational safety rails for coding and UI agents                                                                                                        \n                                                                                \n  If you are building, deploying, or testing autonomous AI agents, you need to understand how systems engineering and SRE practices are merging with AI evaluation.                     \n                                                                                                                                             \n  🕐 Chapters                                                                                                                                                                           \n  0:00 – Introduction                                             \n  0:30 – The Original LLM Eval Pipeline\n  0:55 – Why Agents Break Traditional Evals\n  1:57 – The Big Shift: Outputs vs. Trajectories                                                                                                                                        \n  3:10 – Trace Grading & Eval-Driven Development\n  4:14 – Modern Agentic Eval Architecture                                                                                                                                               \n  5:17 – Case Studies: Coding & UI Agents                         \n  6:19 – The Future of Agentic Evaluation                                                                                                                                               \n                     \n                                                                                                                                                                                       #AgenticEvals #AIagents #AI #MachineLearning #AIEngineering #AreAgentsSafe #OpenAI #ClaudeCode #HermesAgent #AgenticEngineering #LLMJudges",
